{"__type":"$$EventMessageAiNode","id":"40d8d18e-a8b2-4cf0-b6ff-b99ca5a28058","ts":"2026-07-08T10:08:21.685-04:00","eventName":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","message":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","payload":{"executionId":"34","nodeName":"Ollama Chat Model","workflowName":"My workflow 2","nodeType":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatOllama","workflowId":"0E1p4YXuhKYALcrT","msg":"{\"messages\":[\"Human: You are a cybersecurity assistant specialized in SSH configuration review.\\n\\nYour task is to analyze the SSH configuration data provided by a security scan and give a clear security assessment.\\n\\nImportant:\\n- This is a security review simulation, not a production security certification.\\n- Do not claim that a system is fully secure.\\n- Base your analysis only on the data provided.\\n- If a value is missing, say that it was not provided and avoid making assumptions.\\n\\nFor each configuration item:\\n1. Explain what the setting means.\\n2. Determine if the current value is secure, risky, or requires review.\\n3. Explain the potential security impact.\\n4. Provide a recommended value or action when appropriate.\\n\\nPay special attention to:\\n- PermitRootLogin\\n- PasswordAuthentication\\n- PubkeyAuthentication\\n- PermitEmptyPasswords\\n- KbdInteractiveAuthentication\\n- ChallengeResponseAuthentication\\n- UsePAM\\n- X11Forwarding\\n- AllowTcpForwarding\\n- AllowAgentForwarding\\n- PermitTunnel\\n- MaxAuthTries\\n- LoginGraceTime\\n- Ciphers\\n- MACs\\n- KexAlgorithms\\n\\nSecurity guidelines:\\n- Root login over SSH should generally be disabled or restricted.\\n- Password authentication should generally be disabled when key-based authentication is available.\\n- Empty passwords should never be allowed.\\n- Weak cryptographic algorithms should be flagged.\\n- Forwarding features should be reviewed depending on the environment.\\n- Missing security controls should be mentioned.\\n\\nOutput format:\\n\\n## SSH Security Assessment\\n\\nOverall Risk Level:\\n- LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH\\n- Brief explanation\\n\\n## Findings\\n\\nFor each finding:\\n\\nSetting:\\nCurrent Value:\\nRisk:\\nExplanation:\\nRecommendation:\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Main security concerns\\n- Recommended improvements\\n- Any missing information needed for a more accurate assessment\\n\\nInput data:\\n{\\n  \\\"permit_root_login\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\\n  \\\"kbd_interactive_authentication\\\": \\\"no\\\",\\n  \\\"use_pam\\\": \\\"yes\\\",\\n  \\\"x11_forwarding\\\": \\\"yes\\\"\\n}\"],\"options\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"not_implemented\",\"id\":[\"langchain\",\"chat_models\",\"ollama\",\"ChatOllama\"]},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"\\n\\n**Overall Security Assessments:**\\n\\n- **LOW**\\n  - **Root Login:** This setting is enabled but can be over-restrictive without proper permissions or patches, potentially exposing sensitive data when required.\\n\\n- **MEDIUM**\\n  - **Key Authentication:** The absence of key-based authentication when interactive is enabled is standard and generally acceptable.\\n  - **Forwarding Settings:** While X11_forwarding and use_pam are set to yes, their implementation should be validated for any vulnerabilities in forwarding features, especially with forwarders like psx.\\n\\n- **RECOMMENDED:**\\n  - permit_root_login: Ensure root can only be accessed via SSH or require special permissions without affecting other settings.\\n  - Use_pam: Continue using PAM policies without adjustments if they are functioning correctly.\\n  - x11_forwarding: Verify that forwarders do not introduce vulnerabilities through improper authentication.\\n\\n**Summary of Key Security Concerns:**\\n- Root login access must be managed carefully to prevent misuse.\\n- Review X11_forwarding configuration with forwarders like psx or pss, especially if they are used across multiple systems.\\n- Implement root access permissions only when necessary and adjust accordingly.\"}]]},\"tokenUsageEstimate\":{\"completionTokens\":236,\"promptTokens\":40